  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In 2012, a cross-sectional survey sampling 1,966 community-dwelling old people was conducted.
      Structurized questionnaires were interviewed face-to-face by well-trained staffs. An
      overnight fasting blood were obtained for biochemistry parameters.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
